1
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:17,033
Eden is happy now.

2
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:19,533
My daughter is happy now.

3
00:00:20,033 --> 00:00:22,433
She doesn't need me anymore.

4
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:24,767
Eden no longer needs me.

5
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:28,433
Now I want to see how far
she can go.

6
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:29,800
I want to drain her strength

7
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:32,200
until she crumbles
to the ground.

8
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,700
What do you want me to do?

9
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:39,533
Have you seen your mom?

10
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,400
No. Why?

11
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:42,133
I've been looking for her.

12
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:45,600
She went out with Sir Zandro.

13
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:46,867
At this time?

14
00:00:46,933 --> 00:00:47,567
Surprise!

15
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:49,700
Surprise, Amanda.

16
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:50,633
You didn't surprise me.

17
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:52,533
I know you're behind all this.

18
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:55,833
I just want to see you
for the last time.

19
00:00:55,900 --> 00:00:57,533
You shouldn't have dragged
my daughter into this.

20
00:00:57,600 --> 00:00:59,133
You don't have the right
to poison her mind!

21
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,567
She made the decision to
cut you off from her life.

22
00:01:01,633 --> 00:01:02,467
Do you know why?

23
00:01:02,533 --> 00:01:05,467
Because you're worthless.

24
00:01:13,733 --> 00:01:15,700
Yen, what's wrong?

25
00:01:15,767 --> 00:01:18,033
I had a dream that
my mom was in danger!

26
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,900
She needs my help.

27
00:01:19,967 --> 00:01:23,333
Well, I guess it's about time
you think about your child.

28
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:25,600
I can't help but
think about her.

29
00:01:25,667 --> 00:01:27,533
I still care for her.

30
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:29,433
That child is carrying
our blood.

31
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:32,133
She hates that child.

32
00:01:36,467 --> 00:01:37,600
What is going on?

33
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:39,200
Stay in the car.

34
00:01:39,467 --> 00:01:41,100
Miss, are you okay?

35
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:55,600
- Hey!
- Miss.

36
00:01:55,667 --> 00:01:56,833
- Yen.
- What are you doing?

37
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:58,333
Can you please get
out of the way?

38
00:01:58,800 --> 00:01:59,733
Get back in the car.

39
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:09,967
Get back in the car.

40
00:02:10,033 --> 00:02:11,133
Don't look at ugly people.

41
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:12,533
I don't want my grandchild
to come out ugly.

42
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:13,800
Please, get back in the car.

43
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:14,633
Come on, Yen.
- We might get late.
- Miss.

44
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:16,767
Get out of the way!

45
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:17,733
Hey!

46
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:18,833
- Poor thing.
- Get back, in the car!

47
00:02:19,367 --> 00:02:19,967
Get out of the way.

48
00:02:20,033 --> 00:02:21,467
Or you'll get run over.

49
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:26,200
My God! What a crazy person!

50
00:02:26,633 --> 00:02:27,767
Get out of the way!

51
00:03:04,867 --> 00:03:06,267
Your baby is doing good.

52
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:07,900
The heartbeat is normal.

53
00:03:07,967 --> 00:03:11,200
Your baby is starting to form
the brain and the spinal column.

54
00:03:11,267 --> 00:03:13,767
I told you, our baby's okay.

55
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:15,100
But you still have
to be careful.

56
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:17,300
I barely do anything.

57
00:03:17,867 --> 00:03:18,633
Don't worry.

58
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:20,533
We're here to take care of you.

59
00:03:21,133 --> 00:03:22,067
You are lucky, Eden.

60
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:24,000
Red is always there for you.

61
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:27,267
That's true.
Indeed, Doctor.

62
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,333
She's very fortunate
to have us.

63
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:34,200
Because we're taking good care
of her and my grandchild.

64
00:03:34,267 --> 00:03:38,000
After all, we are family.

65
00:03:39,433 --> 00:03:40,700
You are right, Rina.

66
00:03:40,767 --> 00:03:43,567
I'm amazed at how you're
taking care of Eden.

67
00:03:43,633 --> 00:03:46,400
And not all mother-in-laws
are like you.

68
00:03:46,467 --> 00:03:47,833
Of course, Doc.

69
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:49,767
I know.

70
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:54,567
Even though we've been
through tough times,

71
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:56,167
I'm sure we'll get through it.

72
00:03:56,233 --> 00:03:58,667
Because we've
forgiven each other.

73
00:03:58,733 --> 00:04:00,333
Thank you, Auntie.

74
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:02,933
I owe you all of this.

75
00:04:03,733 --> 00:04:05,200
I told you.

76
00:04:06,300 --> 00:04:10,100
I am better than
your mother.

77
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:33,233
Red, I think the lady we
saw earlier was my mom.

78
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:35,600
Do you still want
to look for her?

79
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:41,467
Red, tell her that this
isn't good for her.

80
00:04:42,867 --> 00:04:43,833
Come on, Yen.

81
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:44,500
- You have to get some rest.
- If you like,

82
00:04:44,567 --> 00:04:45,533
I'll go and look for her.

83
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:47,233
You two should go home.

84
00:04:47,867 --> 00:04:49,700
I'll call Zandro.

85
00:04:49,767 --> 00:04:51,667
He can help me
look for her.

86
00:04:51,733 --> 00:04:52,967
Don't you think
that's a good idea?

87
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,600
Yeah, Mom.

88
00:04:54,667 --> 00:04:56,500
- I'll see you at home.
- Yeah, get back in the car.

89
00:04:57,567 --> 00:05:00,633
- Eden, go on.
- Let's go, Yen.

90
00:05:02,367 --> 00:05:03,667
I'll take care
of everything.

91
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:05,467
You're good, Mom?
Yes, yes, yes.

92
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,200
You two should go home.

93
00:05:07,267 --> 00:05:08,767
Get some rest, okay?

94
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,767
Think about my grandchild.

95
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,733
- Go on, go home.
- Auntie, look for her, okay?

96
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,800
I will. Go on.

97
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,133
Go.

98
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:33,933
I can't believe her.

99
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,100
She still wants to find Amanda.

100
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,100
Gosh.

101
00:05:42,733 --> 00:05:43,833
Zandro.

102
00:05:44,967 --> 00:05:45,867
Zandro.

103
00:05:46,433 --> 00:05:47,067
Yes?

104
00:05:47,633 --> 00:05:48,633
Come get me.

105
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:51,367
I'm on the street from
the doctor's clinic.

106
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:52,033
Yes.

107
00:05:53,133 --> 00:06:00,533
I got off the car because
I think we saw Amanda earlier.

108
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:04,067
Rina, it's been days
since we tortured her.

109
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:05,767
We should have gotten
a report by now

110
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:06,867
if she's around here.

111
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:09,100
Well, that would have
been good news, right?

112
00:06:09,467 --> 00:06:12,333
Well, she deserves that too!

113
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:14,533
What if she died?

114
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,100
She would have been stinking
by now if she did.

115
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:17,967
She would smell like a dead rat.

116
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,833
And then people will find
her body.

117
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:21,733
What are you thinking?

118
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,400
Well, you have a point.

119
00:06:23,467 --> 00:06:24,633
Do you know what
you should do?

120
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:29,067
You should get to work.

121
00:06:29,767 --> 00:06:32,667
Make sure you collect
our money today.

122
00:06:32,733 --> 00:06:38,100
Because our patrons' loans

123
00:06:38,167 --> 00:06:40,533
from Casino Madrid
are piling up.

124
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:47,800
Maybe you need to torture one
of them to learn their lesson.

125
00:06:47,867 --> 00:06:49,167
Do you understand?

126
00:06:49,233 --> 00:06:50,433
Don't worry.

127
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,633
I'll take care of it.

128
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:53,800
I've collected some
money already.

129
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:55,300
Please, Zandro.

130
00:06:55,933 --> 00:06:57,167
Update me.

131
00:06:57,233 --> 00:07:00,567
But I want good news, okay?

132
00:07:00,633 --> 00:07:01,133
Okay.

133
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:03,900
I want to hear the good news!

134
00:07:03,967 --> 00:07:05,167
Bye!

135
00:07:08,433 --> 00:07:11,167
Excuse me! The road is wide...

136
00:07:14,433 --> 00:07:15,633
Amanda!

137
00:07:16,267 --> 00:07:17,500
Oh my God!

138
00:07:17,933 --> 00:07:19,000
It is you.

139
00:07:19,067 --> 00:07:20,833
- You're still alive.
- This is all your fault!

140
00:07:20,900 --> 00:07:22,433
You and your brother
did this to me.

141
00:07:23,033 --> 00:07:24,367
No, Amanda.

142
00:07:24,433 --> 00:07:26,500
Do you know what
you call this?

143
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:28,200
This is karma!

144
00:07:28,867 --> 00:07:29,700
Karma!

145
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:31,267
Do you know why?

146
00:07:31,867 --> 00:07:34,167
Because you're a
worthless mother.

147
00:07:34,233 --> 00:07:37,667
You're not a good mother,
Amanda.

148
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:39,933
Your daughter doesn't
care about you anymore.

149
00:07:40,500 --> 00:07:42,967
She hates you now, Amanda.

150
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:44,300
She doesn't love
you anymore.

151
00:07:44,867 --> 00:07:46,467
Do you know what you did?

152
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:50,500
Eden almost lost her child.

153
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:53,700
And you put your own
child's life in danger.

154
00:07:53,767 --> 00:07:55,300
It's all your fault.

155
00:07:55,733 --> 00:08:00,867
- It's all your fault, Amanda.
- I didn't mean to do that.

156
00:08:02,133 --> 00:08:05,800
I didn't mean to do it.
I'm sorry.

157
00:08:06,633 --> 00:08:08,433
Your apology doesn't
mean anything.

158
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:11,633
Eden won't accept
your apology.

159
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:14,233
She hates you now, Amanda.

160
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:15,567
She doesn't love
you anymore.

161
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:17,167
And you know what
else you did?

162
00:08:17,233 --> 00:08:19,333
Your daughter loves
my son so much,

163
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,833
but you forbid
her to love him.

164
00:08:21,933 --> 00:08:23,400
You kicked her
out of the house.

165
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:25,733
You're a bad mother!

166
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:27,167
She doesn't love
you anymore.

167
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:30,500
She doesn't love
you anymore, Amanda.

168
00:08:31,933 --> 00:08:33,967
I love my daughter.

169
00:08:34,033 --> 00:08:37,133
God knows how much I love her.

170
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:42,933
What happened was an accident.
I didn't mean to hurt her.

171
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:43,900
I'm sorry!

172
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,967
Sorry.

173
00:08:46,033 --> 00:08:49,333
- Your apology won't work.
- Sorry.

174
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:52,233
She doesn't love
you anymore.

175
00:08:52,867 --> 00:08:55,633
Your daughter doesn't
love you anymore.

176
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,967
Yen, let's go back inside.
Come on.

177
00:08:58,033 --> 00:08:58,567
Come on.

178
00:08:58,633 --> 00:08:59,700
Come with me.

179
00:09:03,067 --> 00:09:03,467
Yen.
Oh my God!

180
00:09:04,233 --> 00:09:05,367
- Yen!
- Oh my God!

181
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:07,100
- Our baby!
 - Move away! What's going on?

182
00:09:07,167 --> 00:09:07,967
Yen!

183
00:09:08,033 --> 00:09:09,300
Let's bring her
to the hospital!

184
00:09:09,367 --> 00:09:10,600
Go now! Go!

185
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:21,500
Poor Amanda.

186
00:09:22,133 --> 00:09:26,367
You are so all alone
in this world.

187
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:27,900
You know what?

188
00:09:29,233 --> 00:09:32,100
If I were you, Amanda...

189
00:09:32,367 --> 00:09:33,267
come here.

190
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:40,500
Cross the road and let
yourself get hit by a car.

191
00:09:40,567 --> 00:09:42,433
That's what you should do, okay?

192
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:43,833
Go and kill yourself.

193
00:09:43,900 --> 00:09:46,900
Cross the road and
get hit by a car!

194
00:09:46,967 --> 00:09:48,533
Go kill yourself, Amanda!

195
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:21,300
Goodbye, Amanda.

196
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:31,167
A homeless person?

197
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:34,933
Yes, as in.

198
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:40,933
She stunk so bad,
and she was so dirty!

199
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,467
So that's what happened.

200
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:45,500
That's why no one reported us.

201
00:10:45,567 --> 00:10:46,700
So everything's good.

202
00:10:46,767 --> 00:10:47,767
We're off the hook.

203
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:49,233
Right?

204
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:52,867
I'm so glad that
fate is on our side.

205
00:10:54,167 --> 00:10:57,000
Justice is served.

206
00:10:58,167 --> 00:11:01,867
But I'm not done yet.

207
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:08,367
Because I still
have her daughter.

208
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,933
Rina, do you still
have plans for her?

209
00:11:12,533 --> 00:11:13,767
Of course.

210
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:20,467
So please, don't
mess it up.

211
00:11:23,067 --> 00:11:24,667
Mom, I heard you guys.

212
00:11:24,733 --> 00:11:26,367
What are you two
talking about?

213
00:11:28,867 --> 00:11:33,267
Your Uncle wants to
borrow my car again.

214
00:11:33,333 --> 00:11:36,833
So I told him to
please be careful.

215
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:40,867
I didn't want him
to mess up my car.

216
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:45,533
And by the way, were you out?

217
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:46,833
Where have you been?

218
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:47,933
Oh.

219
00:11:48,733 --> 00:11:50,300
I just picked this up.

220
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:56,933
Wow!

221
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:02,733
What?

222
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,400
Hasn't mom come home yet?

223
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:05,867
I don't know.

224
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,733
I'm still here in Cebu.

225
00:12:09,467 --> 00:12:13,367
I've been trying to call her,
but I can't get a hold of her.

226
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,267
She's not calling me, either.

227
00:12:16,367 --> 00:12:17,733
It's been several days now
that I haven't heard from her.

228
00:12:20,733 --> 00:12:23,000
Do you know where
she could have gone?

229
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:25,833
No, I don't.

230
00:12:26,267 --> 00:12:30,000
She stayed with me the moment
she got out of jail.

231
00:12:30,533 --> 00:12:34,900
And I don't know
any of her friends.

232
00:12:36,567 --> 00:12:41,433
Unless she knows someone from
jail that was out now too.

233
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,633
She could have stayed with her.

234
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:50,533
How come she's not
contacting you?

235
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:53,167
Why isn't she answering
your calls?

236
00:12:53,733 --> 00:12:54,933
I'm worried about her.

237
00:12:55,533 --> 00:12:58,067
Eden, don't stress
yourself, okay?

238
00:12:58,133 --> 00:13:00,333
Something might happen
to you and your baby.

239
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:03,267
I'm sure your mom is okay.

240
00:13:03,333 --> 00:13:06,267
She's probably just
letting off steam.

241
00:13:06,333 --> 00:13:08,067
I hope so, Auntie.

242
00:13:08,667 --> 00:13:10,667
I'm always praying for her.

243
00:13:11,767 --> 00:13:13,733
I hope nothing bad
happened to her.

244
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:16,733
Everything happened so fast.

245
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,233
It's all my fault.

246
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:21,767
Eden, don't blame yourself.

247
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:25,900
Something good happened
in your life.

248
00:13:26,433 --> 00:13:29,167
You're about to have a baby.

249
00:13:29,633 --> 00:13:34,900
You will have a reason
to get up every day.

250
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:41,233
You will also have a
reason to work harder.

251
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:44,467
Because someone is going
to depend on you.

252
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:46,900
That's what your
mom did for you.

253
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:48,933
I hope you understand
her side now.

254
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,733
That's God's blessing!

255
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:54,333
Not everyone is blessed
with a child.

256
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,967
Look at me, Eden.

257
00:13:56,067 --> 00:13:58,367
I have no one.

258
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:03,300
Auntie, you're always
joking around.

259
00:14:03,367 --> 00:14:05,733
Because I don't want
to hear you cry.

260
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,167
I want you to be happy.

261
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:10,367
Okay?

262
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:13,033
Don't stress yourself.

263
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:13,833
Don't worry too much.

264
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:15,767
I'm sure your mom is okay.

265
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:17,800
Thank you, Auntie.

266
00:14:18,933 --> 00:14:20,167
You're just like my mom.

267
00:14:20,233 --> 00:14:21,767
You always put me first.

268
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:27,700
I know she didn't
mean to hurt me.

269
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,267
Of course!

270
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:32,167
Because you are
your mom's life.

271
00:14:32,633 --> 00:14:35,067
Just like how you'll
be with your own child.

272
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:40,133
I hope you'll understand
why your mom

273
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:43,833
couldn't accept what
happened to you.

274
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:45,033
I hope to find her soon.

275
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:46,533
I want to talk to her.

276
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:51,800
I hope she's safe.

277
00:15:55,933 --> 00:15:56,967
You've got to be kidding me.

278
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,800
Are you proposing to Eden?

279
00:16:01,533 --> 00:16:02,200
Yeah.

280
00:16:02,267 --> 00:16:03,467
We'll end up married anyway.

281
00:16:03,533 --> 00:16:04,600
We're about to have a baby.

282
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:09,267
Can you think about it first?

283
00:16:09,367 --> 00:16:11,200
Don't you think it's too soon?

284
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,133
Mom, when would be
the right time?

285
00:16:14,767 --> 00:16:17,500
I want us to be married
before the baby comes out.

286
00:16:18,433 --> 00:16:21,533
I want to give my
name to my child.

287
00:16:21,933 --> 00:16:24,233
I want my child to be a
Ramos when he comes out.

288
00:16:42,300 --> 00:16:42,900
Miss!

289
00:16:49,333 --> 00:16:50,067
Miss!

290
00:16:51,233 --> 00:16:52,633
Miss, don't kill yourself.

291
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:57,133
- My life is worthless.
- Miss!

292
00:16:57,933 --> 00:16:59,867
My daughter doesn't
love me anymore.

293
00:17:01,133 --> 00:17:01,933
Miss!

294
00:17:03,533 --> 00:17:04,133
Miss!

295
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:06,967
Please, don't do this!

296
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:08,467
Life is precious!

297
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:12,800
You don't know anything
about me.

298
00:17:12,867 --> 00:17:14,100
You don't know me.

299
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:18,067
Miss, let's talk about this!

300
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:56,100
This is so cute!

301
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:13,233
Red.

302
00:18:23,067 --> 00:18:24,367
When our plane crashed...

303
00:18:26,100 --> 00:18:27,900
I thought I'd lost everything.

304
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:32,067
But I didn't.

305
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,200
Because I met you.

306
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,333
I got to know you.

307
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:42,800
From then on,

308
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:46,867
I knew we were meant
to be together...

309
00:18:48,033 --> 00:18:49,067
forever.

310
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,833
Eden Sta. Maria...

311
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:04,000
will you marry me?

312
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:08,600
Yes.

313
00:19:09,567 --> 00:19:11,900
Red Ramos, I want to marry you.

314
00:19:29,067 --> 00:19:30,867
Congratulations!

315
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:33,833
Congratulations.

316
00:19:45,300 --> 00:19:48,000
I want to spend the rest
of my life with you.

317
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:54,033
Come here.

318
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,733
What's wrong with you?

319
00:19:58,800 --> 00:19:59,933
We were so happy earlier.

320
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,400
Why are you giving
me the face now?

321
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:04,000
You look like you
want to hit Emma too.

322
00:20:04,067 --> 00:20:07,767
Are you happy to see your
son get engaged with Eden?

323
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,333
Wait, I thought you had
accepted her into our family.

324
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:12,167
Are you that naive, Victor?

325
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:14,933
You spend all your time at work.

326
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,233
That's why you don't
know how I feel!

327
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:19,367
I need to spend time
on our business.

328
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:20,367
Or else it will go bankrupt.

329
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:21,800
I know! Fine!

330
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:24,733
That's why I don't bother
you as long as I can.

331
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:29,100
So what is really going
on between you and Eden?

332
00:20:30,567 --> 00:20:33,600
I'm just letting your
son have his way.

333
00:20:34,133 --> 00:20:35,900
Because I don't
want him to be sad.

334
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,533
And I don't want
to lose him.

335
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:43,167
But honestly, even if Eden
carries our grandchild,

336
00:20:43,233 --> 00:20:45,500
do you think I
can accept her?

337
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:50,467
So all this time, you
were just faking it?

338
00:20:51,467 --> 00:20:53,967
Do I really need
to answer that?

339
00:20:55,433 --> 00:21:00,367
Red is only staying with us
because Eden is with him.

340
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:06,333
So even though I hate her,
I have to take her in.

341
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:10,467
But Red has proposed
to her already.

342
00:21:10,567 --> 00:21:11,333
I don't care!

343
00:21:11,400 --> 00:21:12,967
I don't care!

344
00:21:14,533 --> 00:21:16,200
There will be no wedding.

345
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:17,433
Do you understand, Victor?

346
00:21:18,067 --> 00:21:20,533
There will be no wedding.

347
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:27,333
I think I want some cowhide.

348
00:21:28,933 --> 00:21:30,567
You can give that as
a gift to us, Dad.

349
00:21:31,167 --> 00:21:32,233
Cowhide in the room?

350
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:33,800
For your bed?

351
00:21:33,867 --> 00:21:35,333
No, we'll hang it on the wall.

352
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:40,900
- A wall decor?
- This calls for a celebration!

353
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:42,567
Cheers, cheers, cheers!

354
00:21:42,667 --> 00:21:43,467
Cheers!
Cheers!

355
00:21:44,833 --> 00:21:45,533
Cheers!
Drink your milk.

356
00:21:46,567 --> 00:21:47,833
Wow.

357
00:21:49,133 --> 00:21:50,433
I'm so happy.

358
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:53,200
Finally, you are engaged.

359
00:21:53,267 --> 00:21:58,900
And, of course, I'm happy
as long as my son is happy.

360
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:03,600
I'm happy, too.

361
00:22:04,033 --> 00:22:09,167
So I'd like to wish you
loving and prosperous life.

362
00:22:09,733 --> 00:22:11,533
Thank you, Mom, Dad...

363
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:14,233
for all your support.

364
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,600
We really appreciate it.

365
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:18,267
Don't worry.

366
00:22:18,333 --> 00:22:20,067
Even if Yenyen and I are
already married,

367
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:23,000
I'll still do my best
to finish college.

368
00:22:25,033 --> 00:22:26,367
Thank you.

369
00:22:26,933 --> 00:22:30,867
Even though our family's
been through a lot,

370
00:22:30,933 --> 00:22:32,633
you still accepted me.

371
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:34,767
And you took care of me.

372
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:37,600
You're too sentimental.

373
00:22:37,667 --> 00:22:40,467
Why don't we plan our
wedding right now?

374
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:41,700
Wait!

375
00:22:43,133 --> 00:22:44,933
You just got engaged.

376
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:46,800
And you already want
to get married?

377
00:22:47,767 --> 00:22:48,900
Mom, didn't I tell you that

378
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:53,800
- I want to be married before...
- You can name the baby

379
00:22:53,867 --> 00:22:55,100
after you even if you're
not married yet.

380
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:57,067
If that's what you're
concerned about.

381
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:59,900
You don't need to get
married right away.

382
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,667
Mom, we talked
about this already.

383
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:05,433
Can we handle this
ourselves, please?

384
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:08,600
Of course.

385
00:23:08,667 --> 00:23:09,767
Thank you.

386
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,033
Come on, let's eat.

387
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:14,900
Oh yeah, let's eat.
Come on, Mom.

388
00:23:15,767 --> 00:23:16,633
Let's go.

389
00:23:17,267 --> 00:23:18,100
Come on.
Yes.

390
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,533
I'm hungry.

391
00:23:45,833 --> 00:23:51,433
I thought I would forget
you when I went away.

392
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:55,000
I didn't forget you, Amanda.

393
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:59,033
I still love you.

394
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:03,933
Who would have thought...

395
00:24:06,033 --> 00:24:08,000
that I would see you again?

396
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,633
I want to ask you a favor.

397
00:24:29,733 --> 00:24:32,033
Since the baby and
I are stable now...

398
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:32,633
Yeah?

399
00:24:34,167 --> 00:24:36,233
Maybe we can go and
look for my mom?

400
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:38,600
What are you doing over there?

401
00:24:39,033 --> 00:24:40,000
Are you hiding?

402
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:41,600
Who are you talking to?

403
00:24:42,100 --> 00:24:43,533
I'm talking to my Aunt Dindi.

404
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,733
I'm just asking how she's doing.

405
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:49,167
Are you asking how she's doing?
Or your mom?

406
00:24:49,233 --> 00:24:50,667
Why do you have to hide?

407
00:24:50,733 --> 00:24:53,133
Sir, there is a delivery
for Ma'am Eden.

408
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,933
But I didn't order anything.

409
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,067
It's addressed here.

410
00:24:57,133 --> 00:24:58,533
No one died here.

411
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:01,700
We're not going to accept that!

412
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:03,767
Send that back to Miss Amanda!
